ch for\nrobustly uncovering stable causal associations in high-dimensional data in\nstudies with limited samples. Our generalized variance estimator is evaluated\nagainst alternative variance estimators in numerical experiments.\nIdentification of biomarkers with the proposed methodology is demonstrated in\nan analysis of high-dimensional DNA methylation data from an observational\nstudy on the epigenetic effects of tobacco smoking.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 16 Oct 2017 01:13:42 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 7 Oct 2019 03:08:17 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 28 May 2020 07:33:24 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 13 Jan 2022 04:11:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-10"}
